- 'High PE ratio' typically means a PE ratio greater than 20, indicating that investors are willing to pay more for each unit of earnings;
- 'Recent prices' refer to the last recorded price of the stock.

- Market capitalization is a measure of a company's value, calculated by multiplying the number of outstanding shares by the current stock price;
